# Financial Integrity Rules

- Financial writes must be atomic and traceable.
- Never mutate historical monetary records in-place; use adjustments/reversals.
- Maintain balance invariants across captures, refunds, credits, and settlements.
- Use immutable transaction references and idempotency protections for payment webhooks.
- Reconciliation fields must be stored to support downstream accounting.
